 need to check dependencies since I can’t use a Docker service or any optional ones. It seems that the Git executable is an external system dependency already assumed on CI, so I can't add Docker. If a test executes commands, I might need a temporary Git repository. Should I return an \\\"advisory preparation\\\" action because the agent guidance isn't empty? I’ll also ensure the JSON is valid and mention potential risks and deterministic setups. I should check the upstream test POM regarding the `maven-scm-provider-gittest` dependency too.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"No deterministic setup is needed. The artifact is a Maven SCM Git executable provider with normal Maven transitive dependencies; it does not require optional test dependencies or a Docker-backed service. The reported failure is an API signature change in GitTagCommand.createCommandLine, not missing setup.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"If the generated test chooses to execute real Git commands instead of testing command-line builders/consumers, it must create and initialize a temporary Git repository in test code and configure local user.name/user.email before commits or tags. This is test logic, not driver setup.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0471792dffe83825016a2873bcf3f881908913121372eb9bcd\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1696, "output": 1188, "cacheRead": 22528, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 25412, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781035932172, "responseId": "resp_0471792dffe83825016a28739ca83c8190988be09045752f27"}, "toolResults": []}
